CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784607479
OL,3,CWho has Andy Burnham picked to be in
OL,4,Chis Cabinet?
OL,6,FVeteran frontbencher Mr McFadden
OL,7,Fremains in his ministerial post
OL,8,Foverseeing welfare spending and the
OL,9,Fstate pension. He was widely seen as
OL,10,Floyal to Sir Keir, and was at times
OL,11,Fdescribed as "the real deputy prime
OL,12,Fminister" in his time as chancellor of
OL,13,Fthe Duchy of Lancaster.
OL,26,@sD@NOUtD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/34
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30613
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784607479
OL,3,CWho has Andy Burnham picked to be in
OL,4,Chis Cabinet?
OL,6,FMr McFadden, a long-time Labour man
OL,7,Fwho was born in Glasgow to Irish-
OL,8,Fspeaking parents from Donegal, played
OL,9,Fa central role in shaping Labour's
OL,10,Fdirection in the run-up to the
OL,11,Felection. Softly spoken and serious,
OL,12,Fmuch of his work has taken place
OL,13,Fbehind the scenes, though he is
OL,14,Ffrequently relied on to reinforce the
OL,15,Fparty line with appearances on the
OL,16,Fmorning broadcast rounds.
OL,18,F` Angela Rayner ` Housing Secretary
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/34
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30614
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784607479
OL,3,CWho has Andy Burnham picked to be in
OL,4,Chis Cabinet?
OL,6,FOnce dubbed Labour's Red Queen, Angela
OL,7,FRayner returns to the frontline of
OL,8,FGovernment as Housing Secretary after
OL,9,Fresigning from the same role in Sir
OL,10,FKeir Starmer's cabinet, as well as her
OL,11,Fjobs as Labour's deputy leader and
OL,12,Fdeputy prime minister, over her tax
OL,13,Faffairs last year. The Ashton-under-
OL,14,FLyne MP has since been cleared of any
OL,15,Fwrongdoing by HMRC.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/34
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30615
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784607479
OL,3,CWho has Andy Burnham picked to be in
OL,4,Chis Cabinet?
OL,6,FShe was spotted meeting with Mr
OL,7,FBurnham in Greater Manchester earlier
OL,8,Fthis year, in a sign she was willing
OL,9,Fto back his bid for No 10. A self-
OL,10,Fdescribed socialist, Ms Rayner
OL,11,Fchampioned Labour's workers rights
OL,12,Fpackage in her previous cabinet role.
OL,14,F` Jonathan Reynolds ` Business
OL,15,FSecretary
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/34
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30616
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784607479
OL,3,CWho has Andy Burnham picked to be in
OL,4,Chis Cabinet?
OL,6,FMr Reynolds returns to the role of
OL,7,FBusiness Secretary, a role he held
OL,8,Fwhen Labour first came to power,
OL,9,Fbefore he was moved sideways to become
OL,10,Fthe party's chief whip. The role
OL,11,Fappears to have been significantly
OL,12,Fbeefed up since he first held it, and
OL,13,Fnow covers science and technology as
OL,14,Fwell.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/34
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30617
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784607479
OL,3,CWho has Andy Burnham picked to be in
OL,4,Chis Cabinet?
OL,6,FWhen Labour won the election in 2024,
OL,7,FMr Reynolds was at the forefront of
OL,8,FLabour's efforts to redraw its
OL,9,Frelationship with the City alongside
OL,10,FRachel Reeves. As chairman of
OL,11,FChristians on the Left, Mr Reynolds
OL,12,Fhas described his faith as hugely
OL,13,Fimportant to his politics. In 2013 he
OL,14,Ftold the Commons he would vote for
OL,15,Fequal marriage "because I am a
OL,16,FChristian, not in spite of it".
OL,18,F` Lucy Powell ` Education Secretary
OL,26,@wD@POUxD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/34
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30618
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784607479
OL,3,CWho has Andy Burnham picked to be in
OL,4,Chis Cabinet?
OL,6,FManchester Central MP Lucy Powell held
OL,7,Fa number of positions in Sir Keir's
OL,8,Ftop team, and continues to be Labour's
OL,9,Fdeputy leader, an appointment prompted
OL,10,Fby Angela Rayner's exit from frontline
OL,11,Fpolitics. She was the preferred choice
OL,12,Fof Labour members for that position,
OL,13,Fand won it over Starmer ally Bridget
OL,14,FPhillipson.
OL,16,FMs Powell was among the Labour MPs who
OL,17,Fwere early to help Mr Burnham's
OL,18,Fcampaign to return to Westminster in
OL,19,Fthe Makerfield by-election.
OL,21,F` Anneliese Midgley ` Chief Whip
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/34
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30619
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784607479
OL,3,CWho has Andy Burnham picked to be in
OL,4,Chis Cabinet?
OL,6,FMs Midgley will be a member of the
OL,7,FCabinet as she takes up the role of
OL,8,FChief Whip, the Government's chief
OL,9,Fenforcer in Parliament. The role may
OL,10,Fhowever been somewhat different under
OL,11,Fnew Prime Minister Mr Burnham, who has
OL,12,Fspoken of his dislike for the whipping
OL,13,Fsystem used to ensure MPs vote with
OL,14,Fthe Government.
OL,16,FMs Midgley is seen as a close ally of
OL,17,FMr Burnham and was among the "northern
OL,18,Fpower women" he paid tribute to when
OL,19,Fhe won the Makerfield by-election. She
OL,20,Faccompanied him into the House of
OL,21,FCommons when he was sworn in as an MP.
OL,26,@yD@^OUzD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/34
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
