CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784607479
OL,3,CWho has Andy Burnham picked to be in
OL,4,Chis Cabinet?
OL,6,F` Bridget Phillipson ` Women and
OL,7,FEqualities minister
OL,9,FMs Phillipson, a close ally of Sir
OL,10,FKeir Starmer, has lost her job as
OL,11,Feducation secretary, but remains as
OL,12,Fthe Minister for Women and Equalities,
OL,13,Fand will attend Cabinet. In that role
OL,14,Fin Sir Keir's government, Ms
OL,15,FPhillipson has overseen widely-debated
OL,16,Freforms to Equality and Human Rights
OL,17,FCommission guidance on trans people.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G20/34
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30621
SC,0021
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784607479
OL,3,CWho has Andy Burnham picked to be in
OL,4,Chis Cabinet?
OL,6,FMs Phillipson came from a struggling
OL,7,Fsingle-parent family but says she was
OL,8,Ffar from the worst off in her class.
OL,9,FHer upbringing shaped her approach to
OL,10,Fthe education brief she used to hold,
OL,11,Fin which she outlined Labour's mission
OL,12,Fto smash the "class ceiling" by
OL,13,Fremoving barriers to opportunity for
OL,14,Fless advantaged children.
OL,16,F` Lisa Nandy ` Culture Secretary
OL,26,@tD@NOUtD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G21/34
